  <section><title>Getting to know Geogebra</title>
  <p>
      You can access Geogebra apps, which are free to use, in a few ways. Click on the <c>Calc</c> button near the top of this page to open a Geogebra window on the right of this screen.  This can be handy from time to time.  You can also open the Geogebra apps at their website <url href="https://www.geogebra.org">geogebra.org</url>.    
    </p>
    <p>
      Lots of good Geogebra demonstrations are available in their gallery.  We will use some demonstrations specific to this text as well.  For class activities, it will be best to use Geogebra from their website rather than from the calculator embedded on this page, if only because the working window on your screen is likely bigger.
    </p>
